When the document to be filed is the testimony of a witness, each set of the testimony shall, following the party&#8217;s initials, bear a letter (in upper case); thus, the first witness of a particular party shall have his or her testimony
        identified, for example, as &#8220;DOE&#8221; (A); the second witness, &#8220;DOE&#8221; (B), and so on. Each witness shall retain the same letter, however, the first witness&#8217;s second set of testimony shall be lettered
        (2A) and so on;
